<P align=center><FONT CLASS="ref"><B><A 
name=U22></A>[ U22 ]</B></FONT>
<P align=justify><B>Sextus Empiricus, <I>Against the Professors,</I> I.49: 
</B>... Epicurus, although he seems to be bitterly hostile to the 
Professors of Arts and Sciences, tries to prove in his book <I>On Gifts 
and Gratitude</I> that it is necessary for the wise to learn literacy.
<BR><BR><P style="MARGIN-TOP: 30px" align=center><B><FONT face="arial, verdana"><A 
